body:
The Unicorn Store

These are some rambly thoughts on my interpretation of the movie which I really loved.

I believe that the unicorn is a metaphor for self love/self-worth and, the store is the path Kit needs to take in order to find it.

Just like in real life, she’s surrounded by people and obstacles that are tearing her down, her dreams and expectations, because she doesn’t fit into those expectations. That doesn’t necessarily means that the people around her are bad (like her parents) they simply don’t understand her view of the world (I don’t know If wrong but I think she could have some kind of disorder or condition?)

We have people who do have bad intentions like Gary, who made her think she was something special to get close to her and then tear her down on the presentation. So we see Kit trying to make life her life and find herself, while trying not to disappoint those around her and at the same time trying not to disappoint herself in the pursuit of the unicorn - - in the pursuit of her self worth and self love. By herself.

When The Salesman told her that Virgil couldn’t see The Store, it was because of that; because Kit is the only one that, in that moment, could see what she was aspiring to be.

And, despite The Unicorn being something she had to find and build stuff for herself, prove herself - - she did had help, a little push that way. From The Salesman, Virgil, even her parents in their own way–we need others to lift each other up and vice-versa.

This is proven when Virgil build the unicorn house with the help of her parents, and when she was telling the unicorn how it helped her when she needed and how he needed to help another person.

I think that’s beautiful, it’s about a journey of self discovery among all the obstacles while still having to navigate the real world and learning that you don’t have to do it alone, people who reject you included.

Her parents, Virgil, Gary, Brock, Sabrina, The Salesman - - everyone she interacted with, paved her path to The Unicorn, herself.

body:
Unicorn Store

Sorry not sorry for the wave of unicorn store gifs on ur dash but I just finished it and honestly it’s so lovely. The film has a great message that I really needed to hear, and I’ve never wanted to wear sparkly green eyeshadow more in my life?? Seriously though, we all knew Brie is an amazing actress, but she’s a phenomenal director too. And gah I love the cinematography and the lighting and every single one of kit’s outfits


tl;dr: this movie made me believe in unicorns and maybe even myself for 92 minutes
